4 June 2003The Minister of Public Service and Administration, Ms Geraldine Fraser-Moleketi, will deliver a keynote address at the launch of the Pocket Guide to South Africa 2003 in Mamelodi on 6 June 2003 at 12h30.The first edition of this quick-fact, easy-to-read publication is largely based on information contained in the South Africa Yearbook 2002/03, published by the Government Communication and Information System (GCIS).All media are invited to attend.Venue: Mini Munitoria - Mamelodi Municipality, 19481 Makhubela Street, Mamelodi WestEnquiries Crystal Davids (STE Publishers) Tel: 011 402 4292Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)